properties.Title: Online Webinar - Becoming a Yang 2020 delegate in NY
properties.Description:
Zoom Webinar to learn about becoming a NY delegate!

If you are a committed Yang supporter and a registered Democrat voter in New York, you can become a delegate. We need a team of delegates in every district to find supporters and organize petition-signing events to get Andrew Yang and your district's team on the primary ballot.

No political experience is necessary, just determination to GOTB (get on the ballot) and GOTV (get out the vote) from now until the April 28 primary. The more votes you get for Yang in your district, the better your chances of representing the great state of New York at the 2020 Democratic National Convention in July!

If you cannot be registered as a Democrat in NY by Dec. 31, 2019, you can still help as a Congressional District Lead or Event Host.

Learn more about these roles in our Zoom Webinar on Saturday, December 7, 10 am EST.

Please use this link to find your Congressional District:
https://ziplook.house.gov/htbin/findrep_house?ZIP=

Feel free to contact the host if you have any questions.
